feat(admin): Emails tab (Phase 1) — view-only + test send

Adds a new "Emails" tab in the Academy admin dashboard that shows every
automated email the platform sends across the trial + re-engagement
lifecycle, and lets you render each one against a real member's data or
fire a one-off test send.

What landed:

- lib/emailStages.js — single source of truth describing all 6 stages
  (Day -7, Day -1, Day +7 SAVE20, Day +20/+30/+60 REWIND20): display
  name, schedule, mechanism, description, preview webhook + params.

- pages/api/admin/email-stages.js — one façade endpoint:
    * GET                        list all stages
    * GET ?key=X&email=Y         render preview against a real member
    * POST ?key=X&email=Y        send test (BCC info@alanranger.com)
  Internally proxies to trial-expiry-reminder-webhook and
  lapsed-trial-reengagement-webhook, extracting the rendered preview
  from their dry-run responses.

- pages/academy/admin/emails.js — new page. Left column lists every
  stage as a clickable card. Right column renders subject + HTML body
  against the selected member and offers a "Send test to {email}"
  button. Member picker sits above the split (defaults to empty).

- Both webhooks now include `preview: { subject, body, html }` in their
  dry-run responses so the admin tab can render without actually sending.

- "Emails" link added to the top-nav on every admin page (index, engagement,
  activity, exams, ghost, qa) so the tab is reachable from anywhere.

Phase 2 (editable subject + schedule) and Phase 3 (full body editor with
Supabase persistence) are scoped but not yet built.
